uniqueness
proof
set E = ( EqRel (R,I) );
let X being  strict doubleLoopStr,Y being  strict doubleLoopStr;
assume that
A13: (the carrier of X) = ( Class E )
and
A14: (( 1. X ) = ( Class (E,( 1. R )) ) & ( 0. X ) = ( Class (E,( 0. R )) ))
and
A15: (for x,y being (Element of X) holds (ex a,b being (Element of R) st ((x = ( Class (E,a) ) & y = ( Class (E,b) )) & ( (the addF of X) . (x,y) ) = ( Class (E,( a + b )) ))))
and
A16: (for x,y being (Element of X) holds (ex a,b being (Element of R) st ((x = ( Class (E,a) ) & y = ( Class (E,b) )) & ( (the multF of X) . (x,y) ) = ( Class (E,( a * b )) ))))
and
A17: (the carrier of Y) = ( Class E )
and
A18: (( 1. Y ) = ( Class (E,( 1. R )) ) & ( 0. Y ) = ( Class (E,( 0. R )) ))
and
A19: (for x,y being (Element of Y) holds (ex a,b being (Element of R) st ((x = ( Class (E,a) ) & y = ( Class (E,b) )) & ( (the addF of Y) . (x,y) ) = ( Class (E,( a + b )) ))))
and
A20: (for x,y being (Element of Y) holds (ex a,b being (Element of R) st ((x = ( Class (E,a) ) & y = ( Class (E,b) )) & ( (the multF of Y) . (x,y) ) = ( Class (E,( a * b )) ))));
A21: (for x,y being (Element of X) holds ( (the multF of X) . (x,y) ) = ( (the multF of Y) . (x,y) ))
proof
let x being (Element of X),y being (Element of X);
consider a being (Element of R),b being (Element of R) such that A22: x = ( Class (E,a) ) and A23: y = ( Class (E,b) ) and A24: ( (the multF of X) . (x,y) ) = ( Class (E,( a * b )) ) by A16;
consider a1 being (Element of R),b1 being (Element of R) such that A25: x = ( Class (E,a1) ) and A26: y = ( Class (E,b1) ) and A27: ( (the multF of Y) . (x,y) ) = ( Class (E,( a1 * b1 )) ) by A13,A17,A20;
( b - b1 ) in I by A23,A26,CKB19:1;
then A28: ( a1 * ( b - b1 ) ) in I by IDEAL_1:def 2;
A29: ( ( ( a - a1 ) * b ) + ( a1 * ( b - b1 ) ) ) = ( ( ( a * b ) - ( a1 * b ) ) + ( a1 * ( b - b1 ) ) ) by VECTSP_1:13
.= ( ( ( a * b ) - ( a1 * b ) ) + ( ( a1 * b ) - ( a1 * b1 ) ) ) by VECTSP_1:11
.= ( ( ( ( a * b ) - ( a1 * b ) ) + ( a1 * b ) ) - ( a1 * b1 ) ) by RLVECT_1:28
.= ( ( a * b ) - ( a1 * b1 ) ) by CKB1:1;
( a - a1 ) in I by A22,A25,CKB19:1;
then ( ( a - a1 ) * b ) in I by IDEAL_1:def 3;
then ( ( ( a - a1 ) * b ) + ( a1 * ( b - b1 ) ) ) in I by A28,IDEAL_1:def 1;
hence thesis by A24,A27,A29,CKB19:1;
end;
(for x,y being (Element of X) holds ( (the addF of X) . (x,y) ) = ( (the addF of Y) . (x,y) ))
proof
let x being (Element of X),y being (Element of X);
consider a being (Element of R),b being (Element of R) such that A30: (x = ( Class (E,a) ) & y = ( Class (E,b) )) and A31: ( (the addF of X) . (x,y) ) = ( Class (E,( a + b )) ) by A15;
consider a1 being (Element of R),b1 being (Element of R) such that A32: (x = ( Class (E,a1) ) & y = ( Class (E,b1) )) and A33: ( (the addF of Y) . (x,y) ) = ( Class (E,( a1 + b1 )) ) by A13,A17,A19;
(( a - a1 ) in I & ( b - b1 ) in I) by A30,A32,CKB19:1;
then A34: ( ( a - a1 ) + ( b - b1 ) ) in I by IDEAL_1:def 1;
( ( a + b ) - ( a1 + b1 ) ) = ( ( ( a + b ) - a1 ) - b1 ) by RLVECT_1:27
.= ( ( ( a - a1 ) + b ) - b1 ) by RLVECT_1:28
.= ( ( a - a1 ) + ( b - b1 ) ) by RLVECT_1:28;
hence thesis by A31,A33,A34,CKB19:1;
end;
then (the addF of X) = (the addF of Y) by A13,A17,BINOP_1:2;
